  "label": "Meridian Sleeper Chamber",
  "description": "Meridian Sleeper Chamber is a dedicated bedroom set within the Refraction House’s alternating bands of radiance and engineered absolute shadow. Its walls consist of narrow, angled panes that fracture the meridian glare into fixed ribbons, locking the room’s illumination to color and incidence rather than to hour. A low sleeping platform of dark crystalline tile anchors the chamber to the city’s rectilinear grid, multiplying sharp-edged reflections across the floor. Storage niches are cut flush into the faceted surfaces, preserving the chamber’s planar geometry and uninterrupted sightlines.",
